			////////////////////////////////////////////
			// 		Intro
			////////////////////////////////////////////
			section#introduction
				p ThreeSixtyFlow.js gives you the ability to quickly and easily add 3D carousel sliders to your website 
					span.italicIt without
					|  having to:  
				ul
					li Do the math for Javascript or CSS transforms yourself. (If you hate doing math yet want your gallery to appear like it's floating in space this plugin is for you.)
					li Figure out how to position the slider buttons using CSS for up-down or right-left scrolling.  (CSS flexbox solves all your positioning and responsive woes and you can switch these controls on or off using simple true/false statements -- use them only if you need them.)
					li Craft your own animation sequence to make the 3D carousel move on its own.
			////////////////////////////////////////////
			// 		END Intro
			////////////////////////////////////////////

			
			
			////////////////////////////////////////////
			// 		What Else Can It Do For You?
			////////////////////////////////////////////
			section#otherBenefits
				h2 What Else Can It Do For You?

				p The plugin will...

				ul
					li Show more than just images... you can also use other kinds of element blocks as "slides".  (Simply change the 'itemTarget'.)
					li Display dozens of images or other element blocks -- ThreeSixtyFlow adapts and expands to hold them all with plenty of space in between thanks to the power of math.
			////////////////////////////////////////////
			// 		END What Else Can It Do For You?
			////////////////////////////////////////////


			////////////////////////////////////////////
			// 		What This Plugin Does Not Do
			////////////////////////////////////////////
			section#whatItsNot
				h2 What This Plugin Does Not Do

				p This plugin isn't for every developer's case.

				ul
					li The carousel doesn't slide to the next image when it is vertical in any way due to a limitation on the way "transform-origin" works.
					li If you set the carousel to be perfectly vertical on the screen like a pole, the images will rotate so that they're in the right orientation however it's not perfect... yet.
					li The size of image items or other display items is limited to 425px at this time.  (You can change this in the CSS however you'll have to play with the "translateY" and "translateX" plugin options -- see below.)
			////////////////////////////////////////////
			// 		END What This Plugin Does Not Do
			////////////////////////////////////////////
			

			////////////////////////////////////////////
			// 		How to Use It
			////////////////////////////////////////////
			
			section#howToUseIt
				h2 How to Use It

				h3 HTML

				p First setup your HTML file to:

				ul
					li have one parent element with the id of 
						span.codeIt1 .carousel
						|  (the 
						span.codeIt1 .carousel
						|  is a 
						span.boldIt must have
						|  class)
					li under the parent, have a child list 
						span.codeIt1 ul
						|  with id of 
						span.codeIt1 .spinner
						|  (the 
						span.codeIt1 .spinner
						|  is needed for this plugin so it's a 
						span.boldIt must have
						|  class... also recommend using 
						span.codeIt1 ul
						| )
					li have each of your images (or element blocks) inside of each of the 
						span.codeIt1 li
						|  elements

				p
					span.boldIt NOTE
					|:  If you're displaying something other than images, you'll need to change the option of 
					span.codeIt1 itemTarget
					|  from the default 
					span.codeIt1 .spinner img
					|  to 
					span.codeIt1 .spinner [class/ID of block]
					| .

				p See the code example below:

				p You can have as many 3D carousels you want as long as you follow the above structure each time.


			////////////////////////////////////////////
			// 		END How to Use It
			////////////////////////////////////////////
			

			

			//- ===================================
			//- OPTIONS DEMOS START HERE
			//- ===================================

			h2#options Featured Options

			////////////////////////////////////////////
			// 		Carousel Resizing
			////////////////////////////////////////////
			section.carouselDemo1
				h3 Carousel Resizing

				p You don't have to re-size the carousel using CSS.  You can make your adjustments by changing the 
					span.codeIt1 carouselWidth
					|  and 
					span.codeIt1 carouselHeight
					|  options.
				p In the example below we slash the width to 50% of the view area.

				pre
					| t6D3.carouselRef1 = $('.carousel.carouselDim1');
					| 
					| t6D3.carouselRef1DemoSet = {
					|	// carousel parent
					|	carouselDimensionSet: true,
					|	carouselWidth: "50%",
					|	carouselHeight: "50vh"
					| };
					| 
					| t6D3.carouselRef1.threeSixtyDim(t6D3.carouselRef1DemoSet);

				+threeSixtyDim2
					section.carousel.carouselDim1
						ul.spinner
							+addNineImageSet2
			////////////////////////////////////////////
			// 		END Carousel Options
			////////////////////////////////////////////

			////////////////////////////////////////////
			// 		Vertical Ring Options
			////////////////////////////////////////////
			section.verticalDemoOpt1
				h3 Vertical Ring

				p You can change the initial position of the carousel ring... all the way to a straight vertical line.
				p At this time the ring doesn't slide up and down like you would expect however this has potential to create a ferris wheel like effect.
				p Check back later!

				p To make the changes below simply set 
					span.codeIt1  changeInitialRingPosition
					|  to 
					span.codeIt1 true
					|  , give 
					span.codeIt1 rotateX
					|  and 
					span.codeIt1 rotateY
					|  a 
					span.codeIt1 deg
					|  value and ... set 
					span.codeIt1 rotateZImages
					|  to 
					span.codeIt1 true
					|  .

				pre
					| t6D3.carouselRef2 = $('.carousel.verticalRing1');
					| 
					| t6D3.carouselRef2DemoSet = {
					| 	changeInitialRingPosition: true,
					| 	rotateX: -90,
					| 	rotateY: 90,
					| 	carouselDimensionSet: true,
					| 	carouselHeight: "100vh",
					| 	rotateZImages: true
					| };
					| 
					| t6D3.carouselRef2.threeSixtyDim(t6D3.carouselRef2DemoSet);

				+threeSixtyDim2
					section.carousel.verticalRing1
						ul.spinner
							+addNineImageSet2
			////////////////////////////////////////////
			// 		END Vertical Ring
			////////////////////////////////////////////

			////////////////////////////////////////////
			// 		Spinner Options
			////////////////////////////////////////////
			
			section.changeInitial1
				h3 Change Initial Position

				pre
					| t6D3.carouselRef3 = $('.carousel.verticalSlash1');
					| 
					| t6D3.carouselRef3DemoSet = {
					| 	changeInitialRingPosition: true,
					| 	rotateX: -45,
					| 	rotateY: 90,
					| 	carouselDimensionSet: true,
					| 	carouselHeight: "100vh",
					| 	rotateZImages: true
					| };
					| 
					| t6D3.carouselRef3.threeSixtyDim(t6D3.carouselRef3DemoSet);

				+threeSixtyDim2
					section.carousel.verticalSlash1
						ul.spinner
							+addNineImageSet2
			////////////////////////////////////////////
			// 		END Spinner Options
			////////////////////////////////////////////

			////////////////////////////////////////////
			// 		AUTO SCROLL HORIZONTAL
			////////////////////////////////////////////
			
			section.scrollHorizontal1

